## What
Define TypeScript types for Chorus configuration.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] ChorusConfig interface with all fields
- [ ] AgentConfig interface
- [ ] getDefaults() returns complete default config
- [ ] 3 tests pass

## Files
- src/types/config.ts (NEW)

## Implementation
```typescript
export interface ChorusConfig {
  version: string;
  mode: 'semi-auto' | 'autopilot';
  agents: { default: string; maxParallel: number; available: Record<string, AgentConfig> };
  project: { testCommand: string; buildCommand?: string };
  completion: { signal: string; requireTests: boolean; maxIterations: number; taskTimeout: number };
  merge: { autoResolve: boolean; agentResolve: boolean; requireApproval: boolean };
  tui: { agentGrid: 'auto' | string };
}

export function getDefaultConfig(): ChorusConfig { ... }
```

## Test Cases
1. getDefaultConfig returns valid ChorusConfig
2. Default mode is 'semi-auto'
3. Default agent is 'claude'

## What
Load configuration from .chorus/config.json file.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] load() reads and parses JSON file
- [ ] Returns default config if file doesn't exist
- [ ] Throws on invalid JSON
- [ ] Caches loaded config
- [ ] 4 tests pass

## Files
- src/services/ConfigService.ts (NEW - partial)
- tests/services/ConfigService.test.ts (NEW)

## Implementation
```typescript
export class ConfigService {
  private configPath: string;
  private config: ChorusConfig | null = null;

  constructor(projectDir: string) {
    this.configPath = path.join(projectDir, '.chorus', 'config.json');
  }

  load(): ChorusConfig {
    if (this.config) return this.config;
    if (\!fs.existsSync(this.configPath)) {
      this.config = getDefaultConfig();
      return this.config;
    }
    this.config = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(this.configPath, 'utf-8'));
    return this.config;
  }
}
```

## Test Cases
1. load() returns defaults when file missing
2. load() parses existing config file
3. load() throws on malformed JSON
4. load() caches result
